agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"af5dd13ff51f9d578\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01AknbxSAT8gbp5pbvDWe84G\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01Rh1c7xpszhTRjsxy7yAjmU\",\"uuid\":\"4d852c5a-2904-4750-8058-9386094829c5\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T20:36:21.217Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"4d852c5a-2904-4750-8058-9386094829c5\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"8f15321d-2333-415f-a295-a31e4d8776e8\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage\",\"slug\":\"agile-twirling-flask\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_017XX7qPzx5vqDa5tbs7nzx6\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→---\\n     2→name: e2e-triage\\n     3→description: Triage E2E test failures — download CI artifacts, classify flaky vs real bug, create PRs for flaky fixes and GitHub issues for real bugs\\n     4→---\\n     5→\\n     6→# E2E Triage\\n     7→\\n     8→Automate triage of E2E test failures. Analyze artifacts, classify each failure as **flaky** (agent non-determinism) or **real-bug** (CLI defect), then take action: batched PR for flaky fixes, GitHub issues for real bugs.\\n     9→\\n    10→## Inputs\\n    11→\\n    12→The user provides one of:\\n    13→- **`latest`** — download artifacts from the most recent failed E2E run on main\\n    14→- **A run ID or URL** — download artifacts from that specific run\\n    15→- **A local path** — use existing artifact directory (skip download)\\n    16→\\n    17→## Step 1: Download Artifacts\\n    18→\\n    19→**If given a run ID, URL, or \\\"latest\\\":**\\n    20→```bash\\n    21→artifact_dir=$(scripts/download-e2e-artifacts.sh <input>)\\n    22→```\\n    23→\\n    24→**If given a local path:** Use directly, skip download.\\n    25→\\n    26→## Step 2: Identify Failures\\n    27→\\n    28→For each agent subdirectory in the artifact root:\\n    29→1. Read `report.nocolor.txt` — list failed tests with error messages, file:line references\\n    30→2. Skip agents with zero failures\\n    31→3. Build failure list: `[(test_name, agent, error_line, duration, file:line)]`\\n    32→\\n    33→## Step 3: Analyze Each Failure\\n    34→\\n    35→For each failure, follow the debug-e2e methodology:\\n    36→\\n    37→1. **Read `console.log`** — what did the agent actually do? Full chronological transcript.\\n    38→2. **Read test source at file:line** — what was expected?\\n    39→3. **Read `entire-logs/entire.log`** — any CLI errors, panics, unexpected behavior?\\n    40→4. **Read `git-log.txt` / `git-tree.txt`** — repo state at failure time\\n    41→5. **Read `checkpoint-metadata/`** — corrupt or missing metadata?\\n    42→\\n    43→## Step 4: Classify Each Failure\\n    44→\\n    45→### Strong `real-bug` signals (any one is sufficient):\\n    46→\\n    47→- `entire.log` contains `\\\"level\\\":\\\"ERROR\\\"` or panic/stack traces\\n    48→- Checkpoint metadata structurally corrupt (malformed JSON, missing `checkpoint_id`/`strategy`)\\n    49→- Session state file missing or malformed when expected\\n    50→- Hooks did not fire at all (no `hook invoked` log entries)\\n    51→- Shadow/metadata branch has wrong tree structure\\n    52→- Same test fails across 3+ agents with same non-timeout symptom\\n    53→- Error references CLI code (panic in `cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n    54→- E2E tests do not pass when run locally\\n    55→\\n    56→### Strong `flaky` signals (unless overridden by real-bug):\\n    57→\\n    58→- `signal: killed` (timeout)\\n    59→- `context deadline exceeded` or `WaitForCheckpoint.*exceeded deadline`\\n    60→- Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting\\n    61→- Agent created file at wrong path / wrong name\\n    62→- Agent produced no output\\n    63→- Agent committed when it shouldn't have (or vice versa)\\n    64→- Test pass when run locally\\n    65→- Duration near timeout limit\\n    66→\\n    67→### Ambiguous cases:\\n    68→\\n    69→Read `entire.log` carefully:\\n    70→- If hooks fired correctly and metadata is valid -> lean **flaky**\\n    71→- If hooks fired but produced wrong results -> lean **real-bug**\\n    72→\\n    73→## Step 5: Cross-Agent Correlation\\n    74→\\n    75→Before acting, check correlations:\\n    76→- Same test fails for 3+ agents with similar errors -> override to `real-bug`\\n    77→- Same test passes on second run -> lean `flaky`\\n    78→\\n    79→## Step 6: Take Action\\n    80→\\n    81→### For `flaky` failures: Batched PR\\n    82→\\n    83→1. Create branch `fix/e2e-flaky-<run-id>`\\n    84→2. Apply fixes to ALL flaky test files (one branch, one PR):\\n    85→   - Agent asked for confirmation -> append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt\\n    86→   - Agent wrote to wrong path -> be more explicit about paths in prompt\\n    87→   - Agent committed when shouldn't -> add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to prompt\\n    88→   - Checkpoint wait timeout -> increase timeout argument\\n    89→   - Agent timeout (signal: killed) -> increase per-test timeout, simplify prompt\\n    90→3. Run verification:\\n    91→   ```bash\\n    92→   mise run test:e2e:canary   # Must pass\\n    93→   mise run fmt && mise run lint\\n    94→   ```\\n    95→4. If canary fails, investigate and adjust. If unfixable, fall back to issue creation.\\n    96→5. Commit and create PR:\\n    97→   ```bash\\n    98→   gh pr create \\\\\\n    99→     --title \\\"fix(e2e): make flaky tests more resilient (run <run-id>)\\\" \\\\\\n   100→     --body \\\"<structured body with per-test changes, evidence, run link>\\\"\\n   101→   ```\\n   102→\\n   103→### For `real-bug` failures: Issue (with dedup)\\n   104→\\n   105→1. **Search existing issues first:**\\n   106→   ```bash\\n   107→   gh issue list --search \\\"is:open label:e2e <TestName>\\\" --json number,title,url\\n   108→   ```\\n   109→\\n   110→2. **If matching issue exists:** Add a comment with new evidence:\\n   111→   ```bash\\n   112→   gh issue comment <number> --body \\\"<verification details, run link, new evidence>\\\"\\n   113→   ```\\n   114→   Note \\\"Verified still failing in CI run <URL>\\\" plus any new diagnostic details.\\n   115→\\n   116→3. **If no matching issue:** Create new:\\n   117→   ```bash\\n   118→   gh issue create \\\\\\n   119→     --title \\\"E2E: <TestName> fails — <brief symptom>\\\" \\\\\\n   120→     --label \\\"bug,e2e\\\" \\\\\\n   121→     --body \\\"<structured body>\\\"\\n   122→   ```\\n   123→\\n   124→   Issue body includes:\\n   125→   - Test name, agent(s), CI run link, frequency\\n   126→   - Failure summary (expected vs actual)\\n   127→   - Root cause analysis (which CLI component: hooks, session, checkpoint, attribution, strategy)\\n   128→   - Key evidence: `entire.log` excerpts, `console.log` excerpts, git state\\n   129→   - Reproduction steps\\n   130→   - Suspected fix location (file, function, reason)\\n   131→\\n   132→## Step 7: Summary Report\\n   133→\\n   134→Print a summary table:\\n   135→```\\n   136→| Test | Agent(s) | Classification | Action | Link |\\n   137→|------|----------|---------------|--------|------|\\n   138→| TestFoo | claude-code | flaky | PR #123 | url |\\n   139→| TestBar | all agents | real-bug | Issue #456 (existing, commented) | url |\\n   140→| TestBaz | opencode | real-bug | Issue #457 (new) | url |\\n   141→```\\n   142→\\n   143→**Write `triage-summary.json`** in the artifact directory for Slack notifications:\\n   144→\\n   145→```bash\\n   146→cat > \\\"${ARTIFACT_DIR}/triage-summary.json\\\" << 'TEMPLATE'\\n   147→{\\n   148→  \\\"actions\\\": [\\n   149→    {\\n   150→      \\\"test\\\": \\\"TestName\\\",\\n   151→      \\\"agents\\\": [\\\"claude-code\\\", \\\"opencode\\\"],\\n   152→      \\\"classification\\\": \\\"flaky|real-bug\\\",\\n   153→      \\\"action_type\\\": \\\"pr|issue|comment\\\",\\n   154→      \\\"action_description\\\": \\\"PR #123|Issue #456 (new)|Issue #456 (commented)\\\",\\n   155→      \\\"link\\\": \\\"https://github.com/entireio/cli/pull/123\\\"\\n   156→    }\\n   157→  ]\\n   158→}\\n   159→TEMPLATE\\n   160→```\\n   161→\\n   162→Each entry in `actions` corresponds to one row in the summary table. Include all failures that had an action taken. The `link` field must be the full URL to the PR or issue.\\n   163→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"4db85765-2a5b-4e55-8d44-b0410b5cf6ba\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T20:36:21.222Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"af5dd13ff51f9d578\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01AknbxSAT8gbp5pbvDWe84G\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01Rh1c7xpszhTRjsxy7yAjmU\",\"uuid\":\"6f1157da-eedd-437e-a6c2-99d0dc0eacc5\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T20:36:21.407Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"6f1157da-eedd-437e-a6c2-99d0dc0eacc5\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"8f15321d-2333-415f-a295-a31e4d8776e8\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage\",\"slug\":\"agile-twirling-flask\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01THujinKUjSZkUuQeKJo6hG\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→---\\n     2→name: debug-e2e\\n     3→description: Use when investigating E2E test failures from artifacts to diagnose bugs in the Entire CLI, or when pointed at an artifact path for root cause analysis\\n     4→---\\n     5→\\n     6→# Debug Entire CLI via E2E Artifacts\\n     7→\\n     8→Diagnose Entire CLI bugs using captured artifacts from the E2E test suite. Artifacts are written to `e2e/artifacts/` locally or downloaded from CI via GitHub Actions.\\n     9→\\n    10→## Inputs\\n    11→\\n    12→The user provides either:\\n    13→- **A test run directory:** `e2e/artifacts/{timestamp}/` — triage all failures\\n    14→- **A specific test directory:** `e2e/artifacts/{timestamp}/{TestName}-{agent}/` — debug one test\\n    15→\\n    16→## Artifact Layout\\n    17→\\n    18→```\\n    19→e2e/artifacts/{timestamp}/\\n    20→├── report.nocolor.txt          # Pass/fail/skip summary with error lines\\n    21→├── test-events.json            # Raw Go test events (NDJSON)\\n    22→├── entire-version.txt          # CLI version under test\\n    23→└── {TestName}-{agent}/\\n    24→    ├── PASS or FAIL            # Status marker\\n    25→    ├── console.log             # Full operation transcript\\n    26→    ├── git-log.txt             # git log --decorate --graph --all\\n    27→    ├── git-tree.txt            # ls-tree HEAD + checkpoint branch\\n    28→    ├── entire-logs/entire.log  # CLI structured JSON logs\\n    29→    ├── checkpoint-metadata/    # Checkpoint + session metadata\\n    30→    └── repo -> /tmp/...        # Symlink to preserved repo (E2E_KEEP_REPOS=1 only)\\n    31→```\\n    32→\\n    33→## Preserved Repo\\n    34→\\n    35→When the test run was executed with `E2E_KEEP_REPOS=1`, each test's artifact directory contains a `repo` symlink pointing to the preserved temporary git repository. This is the actual repo the test operated on — you can inspect it directly.\\n    36→\\n    37→**Navigate via the symlink** (e.g., `{artifact-dir}/repo/`) rather than resolving the `/tmp/...` path. The symlink lives inside the artifact directory so permissions and paths stay consistent.\\n    38→\\n    39→The preserved repo contains:\\n    40→- Full git history with all branches (main, `entire/checkpoints/v1`)\\n    41→- The `.entire/` directory with CLI state, config, and raw logs\\n    42→- The `.claude/` directory (if Claude Code was the agent)\\n    43→- All files the agent created or modified, in their final state\\n    44→\\n    45→This is the most powerful debugging tool — you can run `git log`, `git diff`, `git show`, inspect `.entire/` internals, and see exactly what the CLI left behind.\\n    46→\\n    47→## Debugging Workflow\\n    48→\\n    49→### 1. Triage (if given a run directory)\\n    50→\\n    51→Read `report.nocolor.txt` to identify failures and their error messages. Each entry shows the test name, agent, duration, and failure output with file:line references.\\n    52→\\n    53→### 2. Read console.log (most important)\\n    54→\\n    55→Full transcript of every operation:\\n    56→- `> claude -p \\\"...\\\" ...` — agent prompts with stdout/stderr\\n    57→- `> git add/commit/...` — git commands\\n    58→- `> send: ...` — interactive session inputs\\n    59→\\n    60→This tells you what happened chronologically.\\n    61→\\n    62→### 3. Read test source code\\n    63→\\n    64→Use the file:line from the report to find the test in `e2e/tests/`. Understand what the test expected to happen vs what console.log shows actually happened.\\n    65→\\n    66→### 4. Diagnose the CLI behavior\\n    67→\\n    68→Cross-reference console.log (what happened) with the test (what should have happened). Focus on CLI-level issues:\\n    69→\\n    70→| Symptom | CLI Investigation |\\n    71→|---------|-------------------|\\n    72→| Checkpoint not created / timeout | Check `entire-logs/entire.log` for hook invocations, phase transitions, errors |\\n    73→| Wrong checkpoint content | Check `git-tree.txt` for checkpoint branch files, `checkpoint-metadata/` for session info |\\n    74→| Hooks didn't fire | Check `entire.log` for missing hook entries (session-start, user-prompt-submit, stop, post-commit) |\\n    75→| Stash/unstash problems | Check `entire.log` for stash-related log lines, `git-log.txt` for commit ordering |\\n    76→| Attribution issues | Check `checkpoint-metadata/` for `files_touched`, session metadata for attribution data |\\n    77→| Strategy mismatch | Check `entire.log` for `strategy` field, verify auto-commit vs manual-commit behavior |\\n    78→\\n    79→### 5. Deep dive files\\n    80→\\n    81→- **entire-logs/entire.log**: Structured JSON logs — hook lifecycle, session phases (`active` → `idle` → `ended`), warnings, errors. Key fields: `component`, `hook`, `strategy`, `session_id`.\\n    82→- **git-log.txt**: Commit graph showing main branch, `entire/checkpoints/v1`, checkpoint initialization.\\n    83→- **git-tree.txt**: Files at HEAD vs checkpoint branch (separated by `--- entire/checkpoints/v1 ---`).\\n    84→- **checkpoint-metadata/**: `metadata.json` has `checkpoint_id`, `strategy`, `files_touched`, `token_usage`, and `sessions` array. Session subdirs have per-session details.\\n    85→\\n    86→### 6. Report findings\\n    87→\\n    88→Identify whether the issue is in:\\n    89→- **CLI hooks** (prepare-commit-msg, commit-msg, post-commit)\\n    90→- **Session management** (phase transitions, session tracking)\\n    91→- **Checkpoint creation** (branch management, metadata writing)\\n    92→- **Attribution** (file tracking, prompt correlation)\\n    93→- **Strategy logic** (auto-commit vs manual-commit behavior)\\n    94→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"c938ff72-cbff-4e97-91fa-ea37f79fb76d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T20:36:21.223Z\"},\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"af5dd13ff51f9d578\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_01AknbxSAT8gbp5pbvDWe84G\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01Rh1c7xpszhTRjsxy7yAjmU\",\"uuid\":\"2f79c00b-74d8-4b21-8b05-5936ff6d9ce0\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T20:36:21.407Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"2f79c00b-74d8-4b21-8b05-5936ff6d9ce0\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"8f15321d-2333-415f-a295-a31e4d8776e8\",\"version\":\"2.1.70\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage\",\"slug\":\"agile-twirling-flask\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"message\":{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-06T20:36:21.414Z\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01BpNWecuWxiLgdKNanpJYUh\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_0177eT3dT119cmaHJYW1VJcN\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.claude/skills/agent-integration/SKILL.m