-running the test to see if it reproduces.\\n2. **No local triage path** — when a user wants to triage failures locally, they must manually run tests and interpret results. The skill should support `mise run test:e2e` for local re-runs.\\n\\n**Goal:** Enhance the single SKILL.md with two modes (auto-detected) and add re-run verification to both.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `.claude/skills/e2e-triage/SKILL.md` | Rewrite with dual-mode (local + CI), re-run logic, updated classification |\\n| `.github/workflows/e2e-triage.yml` | Add `actions: write` permission, increase timeout to 60m, update Claude prompt |\\n\\n**No changes needed:**\\n- `.github/workflows/e2e-isolated.yml` — already has the right `workflow_dispatch` inputs\\n- `mise-tasks/test/e2e/_default` — already supports `--agent` and filter args\\n\\n## SKILL.md Structure\\n\\n### Frontmatter\\n```yaml\\nname: e2e-triage\\ndescription: Triage E2E test failures — run locally with mise or via CI re-runs, classify flaky vs real bug, create PRs for flaky fixes and GitHub issues for real bugs\\n```\\n\\n### Mode Detection (new section)\\n- **CI mode**: `WORKFLOW_RUN_ID` env var is set (from `e2e-triage.yml`)\\n- **Local mode**: User invokes `/e2e-triage` manually — no `WORKFLOW_RUN_ID`\\n\\n### Local Mode Steps\\n\\n1. **Parse user input**: test name, agent (optional), or artifact path\\n2. **First run**: `mise run test:e2e --agent <agent> <TestName>` — capture artifact dir from output\\n3. **If test fails**: Run a **second time** with same params\\n4. **If results split** (1 pass, 1 fail): Run a **third time** as tiebreaker\\n5. **Collect results**: `(test, agent, run_1_pass/fail, run_2_pass/fail, [run_3])`\\n6. Proceed to shared analysis/classification steps\\n\\nNote: Include cost warning — real E2E tests consume API tokens. Confirm with user before running unless specific test names were provided.\\n\\n### CI Mode Steps\\n\\n1. **Download artifacts** from failed run (e